  "text": "## End-to-End Kubernetes Deployment Creation Flow\n\n### Layer 1: Client Library (kubernetes-client-go v0.32.0)\n\nThe client-side creation begins with the `DeploymentInterface` defined in `client-go--v0.32.0/kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go`. When a user calls `Create()` on a deployment client, this delegates to the underlying `Client[T].Create()` method in `client-go--v0.32.0/gentype/type.go` (line 244).\n\nThe `Create` method:\n- Takes a deployment object and wraps it into an HTTP POST request\n- Calls `c.client.Post()` to initiate the HTTP POST to the API server\n- The request includes the serialized Deployment object as the request body\n- Returns the server's representation of the created resource\n\n### Layer 2: API Server (kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0)\n\nOn the server side, the API server receives the POST request at the REST handler. The `REST` struct in `kubernetes--v1.32.0/pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go` embeds `genericregistry.Store` which handles all CRUD operations.\n\nThe request flows through:\n1. `genericregistry.Store.Create()` in `kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/generic/registry/store.go` (line 446)\n   - Validates the object using the deployment strategy\n   - Calls `BeforeCreate` hooks\n   - Calls deployment validation\n\n2. `store.Create()` calls `e.Storage.Create()` (line 526)\n   - `Storage` is of type `DryRunnableStorage` which wraps the actual etcd3 storage backend\n   - This delegates to `kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go`'s implementation\n\n### Layer 3: Storage Backend (kubernetes/kubernetes etcd3 layer)\n\nThe etcd3 storage implementation in `kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go` (line 241) handles the actual communication with etcd:\n\n1. `store.Create()` (line 241):\n   - Encodes the Deployment object using the codec\n   - Applies any encryption transformations via `transformer.TransformToStorage()`\n   - Calls `s.client.Kubernetes.OptimisticPut()` (line 283) to perform an optimistic concurrent write\n   - The `OptimisticPut` is from the etcd kubernetes client wrapper which uses gRPC\n\n### Layer 4: etcd Client & Server (etcd-io/etcd)\n\n**Client Side (etcd-io-etcd/client/v3/kv.go)**:\n- `kv.Put()` (line 113) is called\n- This calls `kv.Do()` with an OpPut operation\n- `Do()` (line 144) dispatches the Put to `kv.remote.Put()` via gRPC (line 156)\n- The remote is a `pb.KVClient` - the gRPC stub for etcd's KV service\n\n**Server Side - RPC Handler (etcd-io-etcd/server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/key.go)**:\n- `kvServer.Put()` (line 55) receives the gRPC request\n- Validates the Put request\n- Calls `s.kv.Put()` (line 60) where `kv` is a `RaftKV` interface\n\n**Server Side - Raft Consensus (etcd-io-etcd/server/etcdserver/v3_server.go)**:\n- `EtcdServer.Put()` (line 139) receives the request\n- Calls `s.raftRequest()` (line 141) with `pb.InternalRaftRequest{Put: r}`\n- This proposes the Put request to the Raft consensus protocol\n- Raft ensures the request is committed and replicated across cluster members\n\n**Server Side - Apply & Persistence (etcd-io-etcd/server/etcdserver/apply.go)**:\n- Once Raft commits the entry, `applierV3backend.Put()` (line 249) is called\n- Creates a write transaction: `txn = a.s.KV().Write()` (line 268)\n- Calls `txn.Put()` (line 300) with the deployment key and value\n\n**MVCC Storage (etcd-io-etcd/server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go)**:\n- `storeTxnWrite.Put()` (line 109) is called\n- Delegates to `tw.put()` (line 190)\n- The `put()` method:\n  - Marshals the KeyValue protobuf message\n  - Calls `tw.tx.UnsafeSeqPut()` (line 226) to write to BoltDB\n  - Updates the in-memory index with `tw.s.kvindex.Put()`\n  - Manages lease attachments if needed\n\n**BoltDB Persistence (etcd-io-etcd/server/mvcc/backend/batch_tx.go)**:\n- `batchTx.UnsafeSeqPut()` (line 145) is the final write operation\n- Calls `unsafePut()` (line 149)\n- Gets the BoltDB bucket from the transaction: `bucket := t.tx.Bucket()`\n- Calls `bucket.Put(key, value)` (line 163) - this is the actual persistence to BoltDB\n- BoltDB then persists this to the filesystem\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Deployment creation follows this path:\n1. **Client**: `gentype.Client.Create()` â†’ HTTP POST\n2. **API Server**: `genericregistry.Store.Create()` â†’ validates and delegates to storage\n3. **etcd3 Storage**: `store.Create()` â†’ encodes object and calls etcd client\n4. **etcd Client**: `kv.Put()` â†’ gRPC call to etcd server\n5. **etcd Server RPC**: `kvServer.Put()` â†’ validates and delegates to Raft\n6. **etcd Raft**: `EtcdServer.Put()` â†’ proposes to Raft consensus\n7. **etcd Apply**: `applierV3backend.Put()` â†’ calls MVCC write transaction\n8. **MVCC**: `storeTxnWrite.put()` â†’ marshals and delegates to storage backend\n9. **BoltDB**: `batchTx.UnsafeSeqPut()` â†’ `bucket.Put()` â†’ persists to filesystem\n\nThis ensures strong consistency through Raft consensus while maintaining MVCC semantics for concurrent reads and linearizable writes."
